4. Why convergence happens

When systems try to reason about reality, certain design pressures appear:
	1.	Memory vs reasoning separation
	2.	Prediction vs evaluation
	3.	Exploration vs stability
	4.	Local decisions vs long-term planning

Any architecture that survives tends to split along those lines.

So independent systems often rediscover similar patterns.

It’s a bit like how airplanes across countries end up looking similar — not because they copied each other, but because aerodynamics pushes designs toward the same shapes. ✈️

